The paper also discusses the use of statistical classification and iterative retraining, which are common techniques in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of conserved features and generalizability, which are relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of automated problem space attack generators, which is relevant to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of feature space attacks, which is relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
